
[1]offensiveness

   OFFENS'IVENESS, n.

   1. The quality that offends or displeases; as the offensiveness of rude
   language or behavior.

   2. Injuriousness; mischief.

   3. Cause of disgust; the quality that gives pain to the senses, or
   unpleasant sensations; as the offensiveness of smell or taste.
